ishop-General Leonidas Polk, the “fighting bishop” of the Confederacy."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Married Henry Richardson Labouisse, 1895 New Orleans","body":"Frances 'Fannie' Huger married Henry Richardson Labouisse Sr. on January 10, 1895 at New Orleans. They raised three sons in Louisiana: William Huger (HD2604), John Witherspoon (HD2605), and Henry Richardson Labouisse Jr. (HD2606). She lived to see Henry Jr. become a US ambassador, dying in Manhattan in 1948 at age 81 before his UNICEF tenure."}],"slug":"frances-huger-1867"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}